I do not support a shutdown of the federal government. I have shared my concerns with my colleagues on both sides of the aisle about the irresponsibility of shutting down the government. In the event of a government shutdown I am not going to take a salary until that lapse of appropriations ends.

I do not support a shutdown of the federal government. I have shared my concerns with my colleagues on both sides of the aisle about the irresponsibility of shutting down the government.

This week, I co-sponsored the bipartisan “Keep America Open Act”. This legislation proposes a four-step process to fund the federal government and avoid a shutdown ahead of the September 30, 2023 fiscal deadline. This is a common-sense path forward.

I am proud to announce that my bill to support Ukraine has passed the House of Representatives with overwhelmingly bipartisan support. 

This legislation includes key transparency and accountability requirements to ensure taxpayer dollars are being best utilized in the fight against Putin.

There can only be peace after Ukraine’s victory and after the defeat of Russia’s invading forces, and we are one step closer to achieving this.

I spoke on the House floor to urge my colleagues to support my bill, the Ukraine Security Assistance and Oversight Supplemental Appropriations Act, to continue supporting funding for the Ukraine Security Assistance Initiative at the Department of Defense. 

This bill passed with overwhelmingly bipartisan support, 311-117 and I'm pleased that we will continue to support Ukraine.
